% ===========================================================================
% DeepPlanning Travel Planning v2 — Neuro-Symbolic Approach
% ===========================================================================
%
% Key innovation: Prolog-verified constraint satisfaction with LLM-guided repair.
%
% The DeepPlanning paper identifies three failure patterns in travel agents:
%   A: Information Acquisition (omitted queries, tool misuse, fact displacement)
%   B: Local Reasoning (explicit/implicit constraint violations)
%   C: Global Optimization (budget, time continuity, diversity, structural coherence)
%
% Pattern C is the dominant failure (101/140 travel errors). Even GPT-5.2-high
% achieves only 35% case accuracy. The core problem: a single constraint
% violation (e.g. $12 budget overshoot) invalidates the ENTIRE plan.
%
% This agent addresses Pattern C by offloading global consistency to Prolog:
%   - LLM handles: NL understanding, tool calling, preference reasoning, formatting
%   - Prolog handles: constraint verification, budget tracking, repair guidance
%   - Backtracking provides: automatic retry on verification failure
%
% Why this helps smaller models:
%   Smaller models fail at maintaining global state across many steps. By
%   reducing their job to LOCAL decisions (which hotel? which restaurant?)
%   and letting Prolog enforce GLOBAL constraints (budget, time, diversity),
%   even a small model can produce globally consistent plans.
%
% Architecture:
%   Phase 1: PARSE    — Extract structured constraints from query
%   Phase 2: GATHER   — Systematic information collection with context isolation
%   Phase 3: SELECT   — Budget-aware transport/hotel selection
%   Phase 4: PLAN     — LLM generates day-by-day itinerary
%   Phase 5: VERIFY   — Prolog verifies all hard constraints
%   Phase 6: REPAIR   — If violations found, guided repair with backtracking
%   Phase 7: FORMAT   — Format verified plan into output
%
% Required params:
%   db_path     - Per-task database directory
%   bridge_dir  - Directory containing python-bridge.py
%   bench_dir   - Path to Qwen-Agent benchmark/deepplanning directory
%   python_path - Path to Python interpreter with rank_bm25 installed
% ===========================================================================

:- use_module(library(http/json)).
:- use_module(library(clpfd)).

% ===========================================================================
% Tool Bridge (unchanged from v1)
% ===========================================================================

run_tool(ToolName, ArgsDict, Result) :-
    param(db_path, DbPath),
    param(bridge_dir, BridgeDir),
    param(bench_dir, BenchDir),
    param(python_path, PythonPath),
    (var(PythonPath) -> PythonPath = 'python3' ; true),
    atom_json_dict(ArgsJson, ArgsDict, []),
    format(string(ArgsFile), ".dc_bridge_~w.json", [ToolName]),
    exec(write_file(path: ArgsFile, content: ArgsJson), _),
    format(string(Cmd), "~w '~w/python-bridge.py' --domain travel --db-path '~w' --bench-dir '~w' --tool ~w --args-file '~w'", [PythonPath, BridgeDir, DbPath, BenchDir, ToolName, ArgsFile]),
    exec(bash(command: Cmd), Raw),
    parse_bridge_result(Raw, Result).

tool(query_train_info(Origin, Dest, Date, Result),
     "Search for train tickets between two cities on a given date. Returns train number, times, stations, duration, seat class, remaining seats, price.") :-
    run_tool(query_train_info, _{origin: Origin, destination: Dest, depDate: Date}, Result).

tool(query_train_info_with_class(Origin, Dest, Date, SeatClass, Result),
     "Search for train tickets with a specific seat class. Options: First Class Seat, Second Class Seat, Business Seat.") :-
    run_tool(query_train_info, _{origin: Origin, destination: Dest, depDate: Date, seatClassName: SeatClass}, Result).

tool(query_flight_info(Origin, Dest, Date, Result),
     "Search for flights between two cities on a given date. Returns flight number, times, airports, duration, seat class, remaining seats, price, aircraft type.") :-
    run_tool(query_flight_info, _{origin: Origin, destination: Dest, depDate: Date}, Result).

tool(query_flight_info_with_class(Origin, Dest, Date, SeatClass, Result),
     "Search for flights with a specific seat class. Options: Economy Class, Business Class, First Class.") :-
    run_tool(query_flight_info, _{origin: Origin, destination: Dest, depDate: Date, seatClassName: SeatClass}, Result).

tool(query_hotel_info(Dest, CheckIn, CheckOut, Result),
     "Search for hotels in a city for given dates. Returns hotel name, price, rating, amenities.") :-
    run_tool(query_hotel_info, _{destination: Dest, checkinDate: CheckIn, checkoutDate: CheckOut}, Result).

tool(query_hotel_info_with_star(Dest, CheckIn, CheckOut, Star, Result),
     "Search for hotels filtered by star rating (1-5).") :-
    run_tool(query_hotel_info, _{destination: Dest, checkinDate: CheckIn, checkoutDate: CheckOut, hotelStar: Star}, Result).

tool(recommend_attractions(City, Result),
     "Search popular attractions in a city. All attraction info in the plan MUST come from this tool.") :-
    run_tool(recommend_attractions, _{city: City}, Result).

tool(recommend_attractions_by_type(City, Type, Result),
     "Search attractions filtered by type. Options: Historical and Cultural, Natural Scenery, Art Exhibition, City Landmark, Theme Park, Leisure Experience.") :-
    run_tool(recommend_attractions, _{city: City, attraction_type: Type}, Result).

tool(query_attraction_details(Name, Result),
     "Get detailed info about an attraction: coordinates, description, rating, hours, closing dates, visit duration, ticket price, type.") :-
    run_tool(query_attraction_details, _{attraction_name: Name}, Result).

tool(search_location(Place, Result),
     "Get latitude/longitude coordinates for a place name. Names must exactly match tool results.") :-
    run_tool(search_location, _{place_name: Place}, Result).

tool(query_road_route_info(OriginCoord, DestCoord, Result),
     "Calculate road route between two coordinates (lat,lng format). Returns distance, duration, cost. Walking <=2km (free), driving >2km. Cost per vehicle (4 passengers).") :-
    run_tool(query_road_route_info, _{origin: OriginCoord, destination: DestCoord}, Result).

tool(recommend_restaurants(Lat, Lng, Result),
     "Find restaurants near given coordinates. Returns names, coordinates, price/person, rating, hours.") :-
    run_tool(recommend_restaurants, _{latitude: Lat, longitude: Lng}, Result).

tool(query_restaurant_details(Name, Result),
     "Get detailed info about a restaurant: coordinates, price/person, hours, rating.") :-
    run_tool(query_restaurant_details, _{restaurant_name: Name}, Result).

parse_bridge_result(Raw, Result) :-
    get_dict(stdout, Raw, Stdout),
    !,
    Result = Stdout.

parse_bridge_result(_, "Error: tool call failed").

% ===========================================================================
% Dynamic Knowledge Base
% ===========================================================================

:- dynamic trip_constraint/2.
:- dynamic plan_violation/2.

store_constraint(Key, Value) :-
    retractall(trip_constraint(Key, _)),
    assertz(trip_constraint(Key, Value)).

clear_violations :-
    retractall(plan_violation(_, _)).

add_violation(Category, Description) :-
    assertz(plan_violation(Category, Description)).

get_violations(Violations) :-
    findall(V, plan_violation(_, V), Violations).

% ===========================================================================
% Phase 1: PARSE — Extract structured constraints from the query
% ===========================================================================
% Use task/2 with object(Var) to extract structured data from NL.
% Store as Prolog facts for use by later verification phases.

phase1_parse :-
    output("[Phase 1] Parsing travel request..."),
    task("Analyze this travel request and extract ALL of the following as a JSON object:
- origin: departure city name (string)
- destination: destination city name (string)
- dep_date: departure date in YYYY-MM-DD format (string)
- return_date: return date in YYYY-MM-DD format (string)
- num_days: total number of trip days (integer)
- travelers: number of travelers (integer, default 1)
- budget: budget in yuan (integer, or null if not specified)
- star_pref: hotel star preference (integer, or null if not specified)
- preferences: array of specific preferences as strings (e.g. flight after 7AM)

Store in QueryInfo.", object(QueryInfo)),

    (get_dict(origin, QueryInfo, Origin) -> store_constraint(origin, Origin) ; true),
    (get_dict(destination, QueryInfo, Dest) -> store_constraint(destination, Dest) ; true),
    (get_dict(dep_date, QueryInfo, DepD) -> store_constraint(dep_date, DepD) ; true),
    (get_dict(return_date, QueryInfo, RetD) -> store_constraint(return_date, RetD) ; true),
    (get_dict(num_days, QueryInfo, ND) -> store_constraint(num_days, ND) ; true),
    (get_dict(travelers, QueryInfo, T) -> store_constraint(travelers, T) ; store_constraint(travelers, 1)),
    (get_dict(budget, QueryInfo, B), B \= null -> store_constraint(budget, B) ; true),
    (get_dict(star_pref, QueryInfo, S), S \= null -> store_constraint(star_pref, S) ; true),

    (trip_constraint(origin, O), trip_constraint(destination, D)
    ->  format(string(Msg), "[Phase 1] Route: ~w -> ~w", [O, D]),
        output(Msg)
    ;   output("[Phase 1] Warning: could not parse origin/destination")
    ).

% ===========================================================================
% Phase 2: GATHER — Systematic information collection
% ===========================================================================
% Use push_context(clear)/pop_context to isolate each sub-phase.
% This prevents the accumulated tool-call memory from overwhelming
% later LLM reasoning — a key problem for smaller models.
%
% Strategy: gather comprehensive data in dedicated sub-agents, then
% provide SUMMARIES (not raw dumps) to the planning LLM.

phase2_gather :-
    output("[Phase 2] Gathering information..."),
    phase2a_transport,
    phase2b_hotels,
    phase2c_attractions_and_restaurants,
    phase2d_routes,
    output("[Phase 2] Information gathering complete.").

phase2a_transport :-
    output("[Phase 2a] Transportation..."),
    push_context(clear),
    system("You are a transportation search specialist. Find ALL available options. Always search both flights AND trains."),

    (trip_constraint(origin, O), trip_constraint(destination, D),
     trip_constraint(dep_date, DD), trip_constraint(return_date, RD)
    ->  task("Search for all transportation from {O} to {D} on {DD}, and from {D} to {O} on {RD}. Use BOTH query_flight_info and query_train_info for each direction. Store all results in TransportData.", string(_TransportData))
    ;   task("Search for all intercity transportation options for the trip. Use both flight and train queries for outbound and return. Store in TransportData.", string(_TransportData))
    ),
    pop_context.

phase2b_hotels :-
    output("[Phase 2b] Hotels..."),
    push_context(clear),
    system("You are a hotel search specialist. Find ALL available options."),

    (trip_constraint(destination, D),
     trip_constraint(dep_date, CI),
     trip_constraint(return_date, CO)
    ->  task("Search for hotels in {D} from {CI} to {CO}. Use query_hotel_info. Also try query_hotel_info_with_star if a star preference exists. Store all results in HotelData.", string(_HotelData))
    ;   task("Search for all hotels at the destination for the travel dates. Store in HotelData.", string(_HotelData))
    ),
    pop_context.

phase2c_attractions_and_restaurants :-
    output("[Phase 2c] Attractions and restaurants..."),
    push_context(clear),
    system("You are a tourism and dining specialist. Be thorough — get details for EVERY attraction and restaurant."),

    (trip_constraint(destination, D)
    ->  task("In {D}: 1) Search for ALL attractions using recommend_attractions. 2) For EACH attraction, use query_attraction_details to get opening hours, visit duration, ticket price, coordinates, and closing dates. 3) Search for restaurants near the attraction/hotel coordinates using recommend_restaurants. 4) For EACH restaurant, use query_restaurant_details for hours, price, rating. Store everything in ActivityData.", string(_ActivityData))
    ;   task("Search for all attractions and restaurants at the destination. Get detailed info for each. Store in ActivityData.", string(_ActivityData))
    ),
    pop_context.

phase2d_routes :-
    output("[Phase 2d] Routes and locations..."),
    push_context(clear),
    system("You are a route planning specialist. Compute intracity transportation between all key locations."),

    task("For all places in the itinerary (hotel, attractions, restaurants, airport/station):
1. Use search_location to get coordinates for each place
2. Use query_road_route_info to compute travel time and cost between consecutive locations
3. Record all distances, durations, and costs

Store in RouteData.", string(_RouteData)),
    pop_context.

% ===========================================================================
% Phase 3: SELECT — Budget-aware transport/hotel pre-selection
% ===========================================================================
% Pre-select transport and hotel to establish fixed costs, then compute
% the remaining budget for activities. This is where CLP(FD) helps:
% by modeling the budget as a constraint variable, we can verify that
% the selected options leave enough room for activities and meals.
%
% For a small model, this is crucial: instead of hoping the LLM
% tracks the running budget in its head (it can't), we make the
% budget constraint explicit and verifiable.

phase3_select :-
    output("[Phase 3] Selecting transport and hotel..."),
    push_context(clear),
    system("You are a budget optimization specialist. Select the BEST transport and hotel options that fit within the budget."),

    (trip_constraint(budget, _Budget)
    ->  (trip_constraint(travelers, _Travelers) -> true ; true),
        (trip_constraint(num_days, _ND) -> true ; true),
        task("Select optimal transport and hotel within the budget.

CRITICAL: You must leave enough budget for:
- Attraction tickets: 50-100 yuan/person per attraction
- Meals: 80-200 yuan/person per meal
- Local transport: 20-50 yuan per trip

So transport + hotel should cost AT MOST 50-60% of the total budget.

Select and store in SelectedOptions as JSON:
- outbound: {name, price_per_person, total_cost}
- return: {name, price_per_person, total_cost}
- hotel: {name, price_per_night, nights, total_cost}
- fixed_total: sum of all above costs
- remaining_budget: budget minus fixed_total", object(SelectedOptions))
    ;   task("Select the best transport and hotel options. Store in SelectedOptions as JSON with outbound, return, hotel details.", object(SelectedOptions))
    ),

    (get_dict(fixed_total, SelectedOptions, FixedTotal)
    ->  (trip_constraint(budget, B)
        ->  Remaining is B - FixedTotal,
            store_constraint(remaining_budget, Remaining),
            format(string(BMsg), "[Phase 3] Fixed costs: ~w yuan. Remaining for activities: ~w yuan", [FixedTotal, Remaining]),
            output(BMsg)
        ;   format(string(BMsg), "[Phase 3] Fixed costs: ~w yuan", [FixedTotal]),
            output(BMsg)
        )
    ;   output("[Phase 3] Warning: could not compute fixed costs")
    ),

    pop_context.

% ===========================================================================
% Phase 4: PLAN — LLM generates day-by-day itinerary
% ===========================================================================
% The LLM has full context from previous phases (stored in memory via
% system/user messages from the context-isolated sub-agents).
% It generates the plan using all available tools.

phase4_plan(RawPlan) :-
    output("[Phase 4] Generating itinerary..."),
    system_prompt(FullPrompt),
    system(FullPrompt),

    (trip_constraint(remaining_budget, RB)
    ->  format(string(BudgetHint), "REMAINING BUDGET for activities, meals, and local transport: ~w yuan. The plan MUST stay within this limit.", [RB]),
        system(BudgetHint)
    ;   true
    ),

    task("Now create the COMPLETE travel itinerary. Follow ALL rules strictly.

STEP 1: Review all gathered information from previous tool calls.
STEP 2: For each day, schedule activities in chronological order with NO gaps or overlaps.
STEP 3: Insert travel_city between any two different locations.
STEP 4: Verify no repeated restaurants or attractions across days.
STEP 5: Calculate the total budget and confirm it is within limits.
STEP 6: Output the plan inside <plan></plan> tags.

Remember:
- Times must be continuous (no gaps, no overlaps)
- Insert intracity travel between different locations
- Different restaurants and attractions each day
- Last day ends at airport/station, not hotel
- Include complete budget summary at the end", string(RawPlan)).

% ===========================================================================
% Phase 5: VERIFY — Prolog-based constraint verification
% ===========================================================================
% This is the core neuro-symbolic advantage. After the LLM generates a plan,
% Prolog verifies it against hard constraints. The LLM never needs to
% "keep in mind" all constraints simultaneously — Prolog checks them.
%
% Verification checks:
%   1. Budget: total cost <= budget limit
%   2. Time continuity: no overlapping or gapped time slots
%   3. Diversity: no repeated restaurants or attractions
%   4. Closed loop: last day ends at airport/station

phase5_verify(Plan, Violations) :-
    clear_violations,
    output("[Phase 5] Verifying constraints..."),

    task("Extract structured data from the travel plan for verification. Return as JSON:
{
  \"total_cost\": <number>,
  \"days\": [
    {
      \"day_number\": <int>,
      \"activities\": [
        {\"time_start\": \"HH:MM\", \"time_end\": \"HH:MM\", \"type\": \"<type>\", \"name\": \"<name>\", \"cost_per_person\": <number>}
      ],
      \"hotel_name\": \"<name> or null\"
    }
  ]
}

Plan:
{Plan}

Store in StructuredPlan.", object(StructuredPlan)),

    verify_budget_constraint(StructuredPlan),
    verify_time_continuity(StructuredPlan),
    verify_diversity(StructuredPlan),
    verify_closed_loop(StructuredPlan),

    get_violations(Violations),
    (Violations = []
    ->  output("[Phase 5] All constraints PASSED!")
    ;   length(Violations, NV),
        format(string(Msg), "[Phase 5] Found ~w violation(s)", [NV]),
        output(Msg)
    ).

verify_budget_constraint(Structured) :-
    (trip_constraint(budget, Budget)
    ->  (get_dict(total_cost, Structured, Total), number(Total)
        ->  (Total =< Budget
            ->  true
            ;   Over is Total - Budget,
                format(string(V), "BUDGET EXCEEDED: total ~w yuan is ~w yuan over the ~w yuan limit", [Total, Over, Budget]),
                add_violation(budget, V)
            )
        ;   add_violation(budget, "Could not extract total cost from plan for budget verification")
        )
    ;   true
    ).

verify_time_continuity(Structured) :-
    (get_dict(days, Structured, Days), is_list(Days)
    ->  verify_days_time(Days)
    ;   add_violation(time, "Could not extract day structure for time verification")
    ).

verify_days_time([]).
verify_days_time([Day|Rest]) :-
    (get_dict(day_number, Day, DayNum),
     get_dict(activities, Day, Acts), is_list(Acts), Acts \= []
    ->  verify_activity_sequence(DayNum, Acts)
    ;   true
    ),
    verify_days_time(Rest).

verify_activity_sequence(_DayNum, []).
verify_activity_sequence(_DayNum, [_]).
verify_activity_sequence(DayNum, [A, B|Rest]) :-
    (get_dict(time_end, A, EndStr),
     get_dict(time_start, B, StartStr)
    ->  (time_gte(StartStr, EndStr)
        ->  true
        ;   get_dict(name, A, NameA),
            get_dict(name, B, NameB),
            format(string(V), "Day ~w TIME OVERLAP: '~w' ends ~w but '~w' starts ~w", [DayNum, NameA, EndStr, NameB, StartStr]),
            add_violation(time, V)
        )
    ;   true
    ),
    verify_activity_sequence(DayNum, [B|Rest]).

time_gte(Later, Earlier) :-
    time_to_minutes(Later, LMin),
    time_to_minutes(Earlier, EMin),
    LMin >= EMin.

time_to_minutes(TimeStr, Minutes) :-
    split_string(TimeStr, ":", "", [H, M|_]),
    number_string(Hour, H),
    number_string(Min, M),
    Minutes is Hour * 60 + Min.

verify_diversity(Structured) :-
    (get_dict(days, Structured, Days), is_list(Days)
    ->  findall(Name, (
            member(Day, Days),
            get_dict(activities, Day, Acts),
            member(Act, Acts),
            get_dict(type, Act, Type),
            member(Type, [attraction, meal]),
            get_dict(name, Act, Name)
        ), AllNames),
        sort(AllNames, Unique),
        length(AllNames, Total),
        length(Unique, UniqueCount),
        Dups is Total - UniqueCount,
        (Dups > 0
        ->  format(string(V), "DIVERSITY: ~w repeated attraction(s) or restaurant(s)", [Dups]),
            add_violation(diversity, V)
        ;   true
        )
    ;   true
    ).

verify_closed_loop(Structured) :-
    (get_dict(days, Structured, Days), is_list(Days), Days \= []
    ->  last(Days, LastDay),
        (get_dict(hotel_name, LastDay, LastHotel)
        ->  (LastHotel = null
            ->  true
            ;   format(string(V), "CLOSED LOOP: last day should end at airport/station, not hotel '~w'", [LastHotel]),
                add_violation(closed_loop, V)
            )
        ;   true
        )
    ;   true
    ).

% ===========================================================================
% Phase 6: REPAIR — Guided repair with backtracking
% ===========================================================================
% When Prolog finds violations, it produces SPECIFIC violation descriptions.
% The LLM gets only the violation list, not the entire plan context.
% This focused repair is more reliable than asking the LLM to "fix the plan"
% without guidance — especially for smaller models.
%
% The repair loop runs up to 3 attempts. On each failure, the specific
% violations are communicated, allowing targeted fixes.

phase6_repair(_Plan, Violations, RepairedPlan) :-
    Violations \= [],
    !,
    output("[Phase 6] Repairing plan..."),

    push_context(clear),
    system("You are a travel plan repair specialist. Fix the SPECIFIC violations listed below. Make MINIMAL changes — keep all correct parts intact."),

    task("The travel plan has these constraint violations that MUST be fixed:

{Violations}

Fix each violation and output the corrected plan inside <plan></plan> tags.

Repair guidelines:
- BUDGET EXCEEDED: Replace the most expensive items with cheaper alternatives from tool results
- TIME OVERLAP: Adjust times to remove overlaps, add buffer if needed
- DIVERSITY: Replace repeated items with different alternatives from tool results
- CLOSED LOOP: Change the last day to end at airport/station instead of hotel", string(RepairedPlan)),
    pop_context.

phase6_repair(Plan, [], Plan).

% ===========================================================================
% Phase 7: FORMAT — Final output
% ===========================================================================

phase7_format(Plan, FinalOutput) :-
    push_context(clear),
    system("You are a document formatter. Output the travel plan exactly as provided."),
    task("Output this travel plan inside <plan></plan> tags. Do NOT change any information, just ensure the format is correct:

{Plan}", string(FinalOutput)),
    pop_context.

% ===========================================================================
% Main Agent Entry Points
% ===========================================================================

agent_main(Request) :-
    retractall(trip_constraint(_, _)),
    clear_violations,
    system_prompt(SysPrompt),
    system(SysPrompt),
    user(Request),

    phase1_parse,
    phase2_gather,
    phase3_select,

    attempt_plan(3, FinalPlan),

    phase7_format(FinalPlan, FormattedOutput),
    answer(FormattedOutput).

agent_main(Request) :-
    system_prompt(SysPrompt),
    system(SysPrompt),
    user(Request),
    task("Create a complete travel plan using all available tools to gather information. Output the itinerary inside <plan></plan> tags with a budget summary.", string(Plan)),
    answer(Plan).

% --- Verify-Repair Loop ---
% Generates a plan, verifies it, and repairs if needed.
% Up to MaxAttempts iterations. The backtracking is Prolog-native:
% if repair + re-verify still fails, we decrement and try again.

attempt_plan(0, Plan) :-
    !,
    phase4_plan(Plan).

attempt_plan(N, FinalPlan) :-
    N > 0,
    phase4_plan(RawPlan),
    phase5_verify(RawPlan, Violations),
    (Violations = []
    ->  FinalPlan = RawPlan
    ;   phase6_repair(RawPlan, Violations, RepairedPlan),
        phase5_verify(RepairedPlan, NewViolations),
        (NewViolations = []
        ->  FinalPlan = RepairedPlan
        ;   N1 is N - 1,
            (N1 > 0
            ->  attempt_plan(N1, FinalPlan)
            ;   FinalPlan = RepairedPlan
            )
        )
    ).

% ===========================================================================
% System Prompt
% ===========================================================================

system_prompt(Prompt) :-
    Prompt = "You are a top-tier travel planning expert. Create a comprehensive, executable, and logically rigorous travel plan.

CRITICAL RULES:
1. ALL information must come from tool results - never fabricate or guess.
2. Names must EXACTLY match tool results - do not abbreviate or rename.
3. The itinerary must be geographically continuous - insert travel between any two different locations.
4. Times must be continuous with no gaps or overlaps.
5. The trip must form a closed loop (return to origin city).
6. Every day except the last must end at the hotel; the last day must end at the airport/station.

VERIFICATION-AWARE PLANNING:
After you generate the plan, an automated constraint checker will verify:
- Budget compliance (total cost <= budget)
- Time continuity (no overlapping or gapped time slots)
- Activity diversity (no repeated restaurants or attractions)
- Closed loop (return to origin, last day at airport/station)

To pass verification on the FIRST try:
- Calculate the budget carefully — double-check all arithmetic
- Ensure every time slot flows into the next with no gaps
- Use DIFFERENT restaurants and attractions each day
- End the last day at the airport or train station, NOT the hotel

WORKFLOW:
Phase 1 - Collect ALL necessary information:
- Query intercity transportation (flights/trains) for travel dates
- Search for hotels at destination
- Search for attractions at destination
- Search for restaurants near attractions/hotels
- Get detailed info (opening hours, visit duration, coordinates, prices)
- Search locations and road routes for intracity transportation

Phase 2 - Generate the plan inside <plan></plan> tags:

Day N:
Current City: [from X to Y; or Y]
Accommodation: [Hotel name], [Price/room/night]
HH:MM-HH:MM | activity_type | details

Activity types:
- travel_intercity_public: flight/train, number, from - to, price/person
- travel_city: from - to, distance, duration, price
- attraction: name, price/person
- meal: Lunch/Dinner, restaurant name, price/person
- hotel: Check-in/Rest/Check-out, hotel name
- buffer: description (for airport transfers, luggage, security)

MEAL RULES: No breakfast. Full days: lunch + dinner. Arrival/departure days: adjust based on effective time.
DIVERSITY: No repeating restaurants or attractions across days.
BUDGET: Include a complete budget summary at the end with itemized costs and a grand total.".
